Polars¬†can lazily evaluate queries and apply query optimization

The lazy evaluation mode is powerful because¬†Polars¬†carries out automatic query optimization where it looks for ways to accelerate the query or reduce memory usage.

Pandas supports only eager evaluation.

Polars does not have Pandas-like index/multi-index

Pandas gives a label to each row with an index. Polars does not use an index and each row is indexed by its integer position in the table. 

This type of indexing helps provide predictable results and readable queries.

#DolphinDB has different read caches on OLAP and TSDB storage engine. 

For OLAP storage engine, recently queried data are stored in the read cache to be accessed faster in subsequent queries; and the cached data of DFS tables are shared across sessions to optimize memory usage.
With data partitioning, #TDengine can locate files involved in your queries based on the time period, providing significant speed improvement for queries.

Your business logic goes in the query. The internals go in the provider implementation.
